1
00:00:05,005 --> 00:00:05,939
Number 53.

2
00:00:06,006 --> 00:00:06,840
Got it.

3
00:00:07,640 --> 00:00:08,875
-Do you need a bag?
-Nope.

4
00:00:08,942 --> 00:00:11,044
No chopsticks, no spoons. I'll use PayPay.

5
00:00:29,829 --> 00:00:31,197
Shut up. Go home already!

6
00:00:33,566 --> 00:00:35,435
How does Aimyon know how I feel?

7
00:00:35,502 --> 00:00:36,469
She doesn't!

8
00:00:36,536 --> 00:00:37,504
A breakup song sung

9
00:00:37,570 --> 00:00:40,373
by a broken-hearted man is
like a staff meal.

10
00:00:40,440 --> 00:00:41,274
I'm leaving.

11
00:00:41,341 --> 00:00:42,175
What do you mean?

12
00:00:42,242 --> 00:00:46,246
When someone's singing at a karaoke,
and they're not good or hilariously bad,

13
00:00:46,312 --> 00:00:47,680
it's the most stressful thing.

14
00:00:48,415 --> 00:00:49,749
I'll end with "Dried Flower."

15
00:00:49,816 --> 00:00:50,650
Don't.

16
00:00:51,217 --> 00:00:53,186
You're making me hate my favorite songs.

17
00:00:56,056 --> 00:00:57,891
I don't want to go back to that room.

18
00:00:58,391 --> 00:01:00,927
I can't forget the six days
I spent with Kyoko.

19
00:01:00,994 --> 00:01:04,464
I won't forget how you kicked me out
after we lived together for half a year.

20
00:01:05,665 --> 00:01:07,167
So this is what loss feels like.

21
00:01:07,834 --> 00:01:09,602
A world without Kyon Kyon…

22
00:01:09,669 --> 00:01:11,638
Don't call her that
after she dumped you, stupid.

23
00:01:14,007 --> 00:01:16,276
Have you finished handing over your tasks?

24
00:01:16,342 --> 00:01:17,243
Yeah.

25
00:01:17,310 --> 00:01:19,112
I've found a good successor.

26
00:01:19,179 --> 00:01:21,881
I'm Kurita, the manager
of Risk Management.

27
00:01:21,948 --> 00:01:22,949
Thank you.

28
00:01:23,016 --> 00:01:24,184
Nice to meet you.

29
00:01:24,250 --> 00:01:26,019
You know, Mr. Ogawa,

30
00:01:26,086 --> 00:01:28,721
I never dreamed
you'd introduce me to Ms. Sakisaka.

31
00:01:28,788 --> 00:01:31,024
She's the complete opposite of me,
but a good fit.

32
00:01:31,091 --> 00:01:32,325
She's more than welcome.

33
00:01:32,392 --> 00:01:34,394
We can highlight our corporate governance.

34
00:01:34,461 --> 00:01:36,729
I'll also be diving into
promoting gender equality.

35
00:01:37,664 --> 00:01:38,531
<i>True.</i>

36
00:01:38,598 --> 00:01:41,401
It sounds like
the perfect position for her.

37
00:01:41,968 --> 00:01:42,802
Anyway,

38
00:01:42,869 --> 00:01:45,271
I'm steadily sorting out
my affairs like that.

39
00:01:49,776 --> 00:01:50,877
Are you really okay?

40
00:01:59,085 --> 00:02:01,454
I've pretty much done all I could,

41
00:02:01,521 --> 00:02:03,990
and I've got a rough idea
of what my future holds.

42
00:02:04,991 --> 00:02:08,094
I even got to meet
my grown grandchild and great-grandchild.

43
00:02:08,595 --> 00:02:10,263
I had a lot of interesting experiences.

44
00:02:10,330 --> 00:02:11,564
It's not half bad.

45
00:02:12,132 --> 00:02:13,266
For a future like this,

46
00:02:13,333 --> 00:02:15,435
your grandpa could give it
a bit more effort.

47
00:02:20,173 --> 00:02:22,842
I wouldn't mind if you stayed forever.

48
00:02:26,613 --> 00:02:27,914
But I guess you can't.

49
00:02:29,382 --> 00:02:30,316
Maybe I could,

50
00:02:30,850 --> 00:02:31,684
but there's Junko.

51
00:02:35,555 --> 00:02:36,990
She'll have hanky-panky.

52
00:02:39,025 --> 00:02:40,093
I'm excited to see her.

53
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:41,361
She'll be thrilled.

54
00:02:41,995 --> 00:02:42,862
But…

55
00:02:42,929 --> 00:02:44,497
don't act like her daughter.

56
00:02:44,564 --> 00:02:45,465
I know.

57
00:02:46,399 --> 00:02:49,235
I'll act like an older sister
just like I did last time.

58
00:02:50,203 --> 00:02:51,271
Hey!

59
00:02:52,572 --> 00:02:54,674
You totally forgot about me, didn't you?

60
00:02:54,741 --> 00:02:55,942
I did.

61
00:02:56,009 --> 00:02:57,677
I wish you had already gone home.

62
00:02:58,278 --> 00:03:00,413
When a guy's just had his heart broken,

63
00:03:00,914 --> 00:03:02,882
he's like the main character 24/7.

64
00:03:03,416 --> 00:03:06,019
You can't forget about him or ignore him!

65
00:03:06,085 --> 00:03:06,986
How's your father?

66
00:03:07,053 --> 00:03:08,021
Ogawa!

67
00:03:12,725 --> 00:03:13,560
Father!

68
00:03:15,495 --> 00:03:16,329
Can I help?

69
00:03:16,396 --> 00:03:17,230
It's fine.

70
00:03:17,297 --> 00:03:19,199
I need some exercise.

71
00:03:21,701 --> 00:03:22,602
Sorry for visiting.

72
00:03:23,102 --> 00:03:25,004
It's just I might not see you again.

73
00:03:25,505 --> 00:03:26,372
So…

74
00:03:26,873 --> 00:03:28,575
is it finally goodbye, Father?

75
00:03:29,642 --> 00:03:30,476
The time machine,

76
00:03:30,543 --> 00:03:33,646
I wanted to use the last trip
for Nagisacchi.

77
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:35,315
You know,

78
00:03:35,381 --> 00:03:37,150
she's been rather down lately.

79
00:03:37,217 --> 00:03:38,084
-Here.
-Oh.

80
00:03:45,091 --> 00:03:47,327
This won't be
the last time we see each other.

81
00:03:47,393 --> 00:03:48,294
Not at all.

82
00:03:48,361 --> 00:03:51,130
In fact, you'll see me again
four years from now.

83
00:03:51,698 --> 00:03:53,166
This is Yuzuru Inushima.

84
00:03:53,233 --> 00:03:54,968
I'm going to marry this man.

85
00:03:55,935 --> 00:03:57,136
I hate to say this,

86
00:03:57,203 --> 00:03:59,172
but I doubt I can approve
of your marriage.

87
00:03:59,839 --> 00:04:00,773
Right.

88
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:02,175
Please don't.

89
00:04:02,242 --> 00:04:04,244
I can't marry her off
to a guy with such wide shoulders.

90
00:04:04,310 --> 00:04:05,278
Are you sure?

91
00:04:05,345 --> 00:04:06,679
Nagisacchi won't be born.

92
00:04:06,746 --> 00:04:08,081
Don't worry about that.

93
00:04:08,748 --> 00:04:10,583
I'm pregnant.

94
00:04:11,150 --> 00:04:12,485
You bastard!

95
00:04:13,653 --> 00:04:14,554
Huh?

96
00:04:15,188 --> 00:04:16,422
