204
00:10:55,321 --> 00:10:56,656
What was your mother like?

205
00:10:57,857 --> 00:10:58,891
Yuri?

206
00:11:00,226 --> 00:11:01,627
She was a bit quirky.

207
00:11:02,161 --> 00:11:03,062
Ichiro.

208
00:11:03,129 --> 00:11:04,730
What did you have for lunch today?

209
00:11:04,797 --> 00:11:06,065
Let's see.

210
00:11:06,832 --> 00:11:08,501
I had my dear wife's bento box.

211
00:11:09,068 --> 00:11:10,236
What did you enjoy most?

212
00:11:10,302 --> 00:11:11,570
Let's see.

213
00:11:12,505 --> 00:11:13,739
The breaded chicken breasts

214
00:11:14,407 --> 00:11:15,608
and definitely the omelet.

215
00:11:15,675 --> 00:11:17,843
The omelet was sweet and delicious.

216
00:11:17,910 --> 00:11:20,046
That's what fueled my victory today.

217
00:11:20,112 --> 00:11:21,814
What do you think is for dinner?

218
00:11:23,015 --> 00:11:24,650
Let me think.

219
00:11:24,717 --> 00:11:26,485
I'm getting a strong whiff of curry.

220
00:11:27,286 --> 00:11:29,355
