to your wife?

221
00:11:29,422 --> 00:11:32,024
Yuri, I love you
more than anything in the universe!

222
00:11:32,591 --> 00:11:34,460
Love you too!

223
00:11:36,762 --> 00:11:38,030
That happened every night?

224
00:11:38,097 --> 00:11:39,031
Every single night.

225
00:11:39,532 --> 00:11:40,766
Even as a kid,

226
00:11:40,833 --> 00:11:43,269
I remember wondering
if my parents were a bit strange.

227
00:11:44,970 --> 00:11:47,640
What about your mom? What was she like?

228
00:11:49,508 --> 00:11:50,576
Uh…

229
00:11:54,513 --> 00:11:56,615
The oldest memory I have of her…

230
00:11:58,350 --> 00:11:59,919
was when I was around five.

231
00:12:01,387 --> 00:12:04,256
My grandpa came from Tokyo to visit.

232
00:12:04,757 --> 00:12:07,626
Nagisa, your grandpa from Tokyo is here.

233
00:12:07,693 --> 00:12:09,695
<i>I could tell my dad was nervous.</i>

234
00:12:09,762 --> 00:12:10,629
Welcome.

235
00:12:10,696 --> 00:12:12,565
Even though I was just a kid.

236
00:12:13,065 --> 00:12:14,400
Come on, Nagisa.

237
00:12:14,467 --> 00:12:16,335
Sit on Grandpa's lap.

238
00:12:16,402 --> 00:12:17,703
<i>I could kind of tell</i>

239
00:12:17,770 --> 00:12:22,942
it was up to me to ease the tension.

240
00:12:23,442 --> 00:12:25,878
But I wasn't sure how.

241
00:12:25,945 --> 00:12:28,314
<i>And Grandpa smelled like cigarettes.</i>

242
00:12:31,217 --> 00:12:32,284
