1076
00:53:39,716 --> 00:53:43,119
He wants it to be just us for now.
He said kids can wait.

1077
00:53:45,121 --> 00:53:46,189
I see.

1078
00:53:50,393 --> 00:53:51,695
I'm happy for you.

1079
00:53:54,931 --> 00:53:55,932
You too.

1080
00:54:05,242 --> 00:54:08,878
<i>Let's be tolerant</i>

1081
00:54:09,512 --> 00:54:10,880
You're late!

1082
00:54:10,947 --> 00:54:12,983
Couldn't you have texted at least?

1083
00:54:13,049 --> 00:54:14,451
Yeah, my bad.

1084
00:54:15,485 --> 00:54:16,419
Okay!

1085
00:54:16,486 --> 00:54:18,054
It's Daddy!

1086
00:54:18,121 --> 00:54:19,522
Here we go!

1087
00:54:19,589 --> 00:54:22,058
Let's go to Daddy, Machato.

1088
00:54:23,026 --> 00:54:24,394
Sorry, he's pooping.

1089
00:54:25,128 --> 00:54:26,263
Change his diapers later.

1090
00:54:26,329 --> 00:54:30,267
Seriously, you really don't have
a knack for parenting.

1091
00:54:30,333 --> 00:54:32,102
It's me, Matchy!

1092
00:54:34,704 --> 00:54:36,940
Excuse me. I'm Masahiko Akitsu.

1093
00:54:38,842 --> 00:54:39,676
Listen.

1094
00:54:39,743 --> 00:54:42,245
You're free to date
whomever you like, but…

1095
00:54:42,746 --> 00:54:44,781
Well then, be a good daddy.

1096
00:54:44,848 --> 00:54:45,682
Bye!

1097
00:54:46,383 --> 00:54:47,550
Shouldn't you hear him out?

1098
00:54:48,118 --> 00:54:49,152
It's fine.

1099
00:54:55,825 --> 00:54:57,394
-What do you feel like eating?
-Um?

1100
00:54:57,460 --> 00:54:59,095
Let me think.

1101
00:55:03,933 --> 00:55:04,834
Hey!

1102
00:55:04,901 --> 00:55:07,037
Wake up, ugly!
It's the entrance ceremony today!

1103
00:55:07,103 --> 00:55:09,139
I know that! Shut up!

1104
00:55:23,520 --> 00:55:24,421
Geezer.

1105
00:55:26,623 --> 00:55:27,457
Cash, please.

1106
00:55:31,161 --> 00:55:32,562
For crying out loud.

1107
00:55:32,629 --> 00:55:34,931
She was only good until her entrance exam.

1108
00:55:35,999 --> 00:55:38,468
And university sure isn't cheap.

1109
00:55:39,436 --> 00:55:41,338
Even if I work hard to cover her tuition,

1110
00:55:41,404 --> 00:55:43,707
she's just going to have
hanky-panky with some guy.

1111
00:55:44,274 --> 00:55:45,608
Are you listening, Barkeep?

1112
00:56:19,909 --> 00:56:20,810
A rat?

1113
00:56:20,877 --> 00:56:24,814
KYOKO KOIZUMI
"KOGARASHI NI DAKARETE"

1114
00:56:30,220 --> 00:56:31,521
Mr. Ogawa!

1115
00:56:32,222 --> 00:56:33,056
Sorry?

1116
00:56:33,823 --> 00:56:35,058
It's me, Inoue.

1117
00:56:35,625 --> 00:56:37,694
Your student, Masakazu Inoue.

1118
00:56:38,228 --> 00:56:40,163
I finally made it!

1119
00:56:40,230 --> 00:56:41,464
I finally got to see you!

1120
00:56:42,999 --> 00:56:44,100
You're Inoue?

1121
00:56:45,201 --> 00:56:46,603
You're old, though.

1122
00:56:46,669 --> 00:56:48,204
You're the same Inoue?

1123
00:56:48,271 --> 00:56:49,172
Yes.

1124
00:56:49,239 --> 00:56:52,342
I've come from 2054.

1125
00:56:52,909 --> 00:56:55,311
I discovered the time tunnel.

1126
00:56:55,879 --> 00:56:58,581
Thanks to Sako sponsoring me,

1127
00:56:58,648 --> 00:57:00,917
I was able to do lots of research.

1128
00:57:01,718 --> 00:57:04,788
Unlike the bus,
you can go to any era you like.

1129
00:57:06,122 --> 00:57:07,490
I don't get it.

1130
00:57:09,426 --> 00:57:10,427
Huh?

1131
00:57:21,237 --> 00:57:22,472
That hole…

1132
00:57:22,539 --> 00:57:23,773
did you dig it?

1133
00:57:25,141 --> 00:57:27,811
Come, let's go to any era you want!

1134
00:57:45,295 --> 00:57:46,796
No way.

1135
00:57:57,540 --> 00:57:59,676
This production features
inappropriate dialogue.

1136
00:57:59,742 --> 00:58:02,145
But in keeping
with the nature of this drama,

1137
00:58:02,212 --> 00:58:04,981
we purposefully presented
the expressions of 2024 as they are.

1138
00:58:05,048 --> 00:58:06,182
Subtitle translation by: Ai Matsuoka

